select * from `users` where `id` = 1 and `users`.`deleted_at` is null limit 1
select `name` from `employee_status` where `employee_status`.`deleted_at` is null
select employee_status, COUNT(*) as total from `employees` where `employees`.`deleted_at` is null group by `employee_status`
select gender, COUNT(*) as total from `employees` where `employees`.`deleted_at` is null group by `gender`
select education, COUNT(*) as total from `employees` where `employees`.`deleted_at` is null group by `education`
select count(*) as aggregate from `employees` where TIMESTAMPDIFF(YEAR, date_birth, '2025-01-04 03:46:44') < 20 and `employees`.`deleted_at` is null
select count(*) as aggregate from `employees` where TIMESTAMPDIFF(YEAR, date_birth, '2025-01-04 03:46:44') BETWEEN 21 AND 25 and `employees`.`deleted_at` is null

select count(*) as aggregate from `employees` where TIMESTAMPDIFF(YEAR, date_birth, '2025-01-04 03:46:44') > 55 and `employees`.`deleted_at` is null
select religion, COUNT(*) as total from `employees` where `employees`.`deleted_at` is null group by `religion`
select marriage, COUNT(*) as total from `employees` where `employees`.`deleted_at` is null group by `marriage`
select count(*) as aggregate from `employees` where TIMESTAMPDIFF(YEAR, joining_date, '2025-01-04 03:46:44') < 1 and `employees`.`deleted_at` is null
select count(*) as aggregate from `employees` where TIMESTAMPDIFF(YEAR, joining_date, '2025-01-04 03:46:44') BETWEEN 1 AND 3 and `employees`.`deleted_at` is null
select count(*) as aggregate from `employees` where TIMESTAMPDIFF(YEAR, joining_date, '2025-01-04 03:46:44') BETWEEN 4 AND 6 and `employees`.`deleted_at` is null
select count(*) as aggregate from `employees` where TIMESTAMPDIFF(YEAR, joining_date, '2025-01-04 03:46:44') BETWEEN 7 AND 9 and `employees`.`deleted_at` is null
select count(*) as aggregate from `employees` where TIMESTAMPDIFF(YEAR, joining_date, '2025-01-04 03:46:44') > 9 and `employees`.`deleted_at` is null
select * from `cache` where `key` in ('spatie.permission.cache')

select `permissions`.*, `model_has_permissions`.`model_id` as `pivot_model_id`, `model_has_permissions`.`permission_id` as `pivot_permission_id`, `model_has_permissions`.`model_type` as `pivot_model_type` from `permissions` inner join `model_has_permissions` on `permissions`.`id` = `model_has_permissions`.`permission_id` where `model_has_permissions`.`model_id` = 1 and `model_has_permissions`.`model_type` = 'App\\Models\\User'

select `roles`.*, `model_has_roles`.`model_id` as `pivot_model_id`, `model_has_roles`.`role_id` as `pivot_role_id`, `model_has_roles`.`model_type` as `pivot_model_type` from `roles` inner join `model_has_roles` on `roles`.`id` = `model_has_roles`.`role_id` where `model_has_roles`.`model_id` in (1) and `model_has_roles`.`model_type` = 'App\\Models\\User'
